Convert Earth Engine (EE) Table in a Simple Feature (sf)

Source: R/ee_as_sf.R
ee_as_sf.Rd

Convert Earth Engine (EE) Table in a Simple Feature (sf)

ee_as_sf(x)

Arguments

x

ee.Geometry, ee.Feature or ee.FeatureCollection object to be converted into sf.

Value

An sf class object, see Details.

Details

The type of sf object returned will depend on the input GeoJSON. Sometimes you will get back a POINTS class, and sometimes a POLYGON class, etc., depending on what the structure of the GeoJSON. The reading and writing of the CRS to/from geojson is inconsistent. You can directly set the CRS by passing a valid PROJ4 string or epsg code to the crs argument in st_read.
